WEBVTT

00:02.437 --> 00:03.742
What's that?

00:03.786 --> 00:05.222
Your copies of
Smurf's will.

00:05.266 --> 00:06.745
You should read it.

00:06.789 --> 00:08.573
What the hell is this?
Who the hell is Pamela Johnson?

00:08.617 --> 00:10.314
I have the current addressfor Pam,

00:10.358 --> 00:12.055
phone number,
police records.

00:12.099 --> 00:13.796
Did I pass?You did.

00:13.839 --> 00:16.146
Adrian: They told me I was gonna
go to jail for 20 years.

00:16.190 --> 00:17.756
This detective shows up,

00:17.800 --> 00:19.497
and he starts asking questions
about you and your brothers.

00:19.541 --> 00:20.890
Adrian: So what's the plan?
Indonesia?

00:20.933 --> 00:23.327
Great surfing,
no extradition treaty.

00:23.371 --> 00:24.589
Is that our only choice?

00:24.633 --> 00:26.069
You'll be dealing
with me now.

00:26.113 --> 00:28.028
Your uncles know you planning
on running things?

00:28.071 --> 00:30.508
They will.Alright.

00:30.552 --> 00:31.596
How's the kid?

00:31.640 --> 00:33.729
I think he's yours.

00:33.772 --> 00:35.339
I'll make sure that everything's
ready for you both

00:35.383 --> 00:37.124
when you come back
to the house.

00:37.167 --> 00:39.474
How come you didn't tell me
you saw Angela

00:39.517 --> 00:41.606
when I was looking
for her yesterday?

00:41.650 --> 00:42.912
J: I know that
you care about her.

00:42.955 --> 00:44.435
But this is
what she does.

00:44.479 --> 00:46.437
She gets sober and then
she falls right back in.

00:46.481 --> 00:47.743
Just like my mom.

00:47.786 --> 00:49.310
What do you want to do
about her ashes?

00:49.353 --> 00:50.528
Deran:
She bought us those burial plots

00:50.572 --> 00:51.964
where she moved Julia.

00:52.008 --> 00:53.096
We'll also be there.

00:53.140 --> 00:55.098
Just seems kind of boring
for Smurf.

00:55.142 --> 00:58.406
I don't think all this
moving around is good.

00:58.449 --> 01:00.625
-Why?
-I think Andrew needs more.

01:00.669 --> 01:02.714
What?
More something.

01:02.758 --> 01:05.456
Your brother's gonna be
just fine.

01:06.327 --> 01:10.157
♪♪

01:10.200 --> 01:16.119
♪ She stares deeply

01:16.163 --> 01:19.818
♪ Locked inside me

01:19.862 --> 01:23.083
♪ Burnin' brightly

01:25.868 --> 01:31.569
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:31.613 --> 01:34.920
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin

01:34.964 --> 01:38.489
♪ Every night now, they'll win

01:41.971 --> 01:44.669
♪ Come and meet my black hole

01:44.713 --> 01:48.630
♪ Got a big black hole

01:48.673 --> 01:52.547
♪ Got a big black hole

01:52.590 --> 01:56.159
♪ I've got a big black hole

01:56.203 --> 02:00.294
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

02:00.337 --> 02:04.298
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

02:04.341 --> 02:06.561
♪ Got a

02:10.304 --> 02:13.133
[ Drill whirs ]

02:17.876 --> 02:20.140
Should probably leave
in 15 minutes.

02:23.055 --> 02:25.580
How'd you find
this woman?

02:25.623 --> 02:27.451
She found us.

02:27.495 --> 02:29.671
She was Smurf's
estate attorney.

02:34.806 --> 02:36.721
Are you going tochange?

02:38.506 --> 02:40.769
You can handle it
without me.

02:40.812 --> 02:42.292
You're good at this shit,right?

02:42.336 --> 02:44.468
Well,
we should all be there.

02:44.512 --> 02:47.732
[ Telephone rings ]

02:50.648 --> 02:52.302
Who is that?

02:52.346 --> 02:54.261
[ Sighs ]

02:59.875 --> 03:01.050
Hello?

03:01.093 --> 03:03.183
Yeah, hi, it's Ken Roberts
checking back.

03:03.226 --> 03:05.185
Is Angela Kane here?

03:08.275 --> 03:09.363
Is this Pope?

03:09.406 --> 03:10.929
She doesn't
live here anymore.

03:10.973 --> 03:12.844
I'm her parole officer,
and it's been two weeks

03:12.888 --> 03:14.672
since she's checked in.

03:14.716 --> 03:16.283
I'm gonna have to report her
as non-compliant

03:16.326 --> 03:19.416
and issue a warrant for her
arrest if she doesn't show up.

03:19.460 --> 03:21.636
I'm sorry.
I can't help you.

03:23.812 --> 03:25.640
He's been showing up?

03:25.683 --> 03:28.643
Few times.

03:28.686 --> 03:30.732
Does she have a key
to the house?

03:34.953 --> 03:36.781
Alright, we should
change the locks.

03:36.825 --> 03:39.001
I can call the locksmith,
maybe the guy --

03:39.044 --> 03:40.742
I'll do it.

03:46.226 --> 03:47.923
Alright.

03:53.407 --> 03:55.060
This is
the last of it.

03:55.104 --> 03:56.671
Alright, Tim gets
10% of the house,

03:56.714 --> 03:58.934
plus whatever
gets put in here.

03:58.977 --> 04:00.675
How much do you think
we'll raise?

04:00.718 --> 04:03.068
Oh, a couple grand,maybe.

04:03.112 --> 04:04.722
Man, if we send Tim outta here
with a couple grand,

04:04.766 --> 04:06.550
I doubt he's gonna
spend it on teeth.

04:06.594 --> 04:07.856
Yeah.
I'm outta here.

04:07.899 --> 04:09.727
I'll be back after
this lawyer thing.

04:09.771 --> 04:11.599
Hey,
how's Adrian?

04:11.642 --> 04:13.165
It's been a while
since I've seen him.

04:13.209 --> 04:16.560
He's good.
He's on a boating trip, so...

04:16.604 --> 04:18.562
No free drinks today,alright?

04:18.606 --> 04:19.737
People around here,
they think

04:19.781 --> 04:21.391
I'm rolling in cash
or something.

04:21.435 --> 04:23.088
Okay.

04:23.132 --> 04:31.358
♪♪

04:31.401 --> 04:39.583
♪♪

04:39.627 --> 04:48.113
♪♪

04:48.157 --> 04:56.339
♪♪

04:56.383 --> 05:04.608
♪♪

05:04.652 --> 05:06.349
[ Engine starts ]

05:06.393 --> 05:12.137
♪♪

05:12.181 --> 05:15.619
None of us know
who this Pamela Johnson is.

05:15.663 --> 05:16.968
I know you're disappointed
by the way

05:17.012 --> 05:18.883
your mother chose
to structure her estate,

05:18.927 --> 05:20.494
but she had the right
to distribute her assets

05:20.537 --> 05:21.625
however she wanted.

05:21.669 --> 05:23.105
She was ill.

05:23.148 --> 05:24.585
Can we contest
based on the fact

05:24.628 --> 05:26.282
that she was on a lot
of painkillers and medication?

05:26.326 --> 05:29.024
Ms. Cody had me
draw this up four weeks ago.

05:29.067 --> 05:30.765
She was lucid
and very clear

05:30.808 --> 05:32.288
on how she wanted
her estate distributed.

05:32.332 --> 05:35.030
So we have no grounds
to contest?

05:35.073 --> 05:36.901
You'd have to prove she wasn't
in her right mind

05:36.945 --> 05:38.468
at the time
she signed the document.

05:38.512 --> 05:40.340
She couldn't have been.

05:40.383 --> 05:42.516
I'm sorry.
There's nothing I can do.

05:42.559 --> 05:43.821
Hey, this ain't right.

05:43.865 --> 05:45.301
Deran: Can we talk to this
Pamela Johnson

05:45.345 --> 05:47.782
and try and work
something out with her?

05:47.825 --> 05:49.349
I've been in touch
with her attorney.

05:49.392 --> 05:52.003
She seems very satisfied
by the results of the will.

05:52.047 --> 05:54.266
Yeah, I bet she is.

05:54.310 --> 05:57.139
What if she didn't show up
to the probate hearing?

06:00.534 --> 06:02.231
She has a family.

06:02.274 --> 06:04.059
The estate would transferto them.

06:04.102 --> 06:06.235
And the bank accounts and the
rental income on the properties?

06:06.278 --> 06:08.280
All frozen until the estate
is settled.

06:08.324 --> 06:10.239
So, when do we have to move
out of the house?

06:10.282 --> 06:12.154
Probate takes between
four and six months.

06:12.197 --> 06:13.808
Yeah,
but it could be faster.

06:13.851 --> 06:16.506
It could.
Depends on Ms. Johnson.

06:16.550 --> 06:18.726
She owns everything.

06:20.641 --> 06:26.951
♪♪

06:26.995 --> 06:30.433
Tony:
See anything you like?

06:30.477 --> 06:32.261
Not sure.

06:34.568 --> 06:36.178
Deejay:
I've been saying it for weeks.

06:36.221 --> 06:37.701
The Summer Olympics
should be bringing

06:37.745 --> 06:39.311
more revenue to South LA,

06:39.355 --> 06:41.444
but all it is bringing
is more police.

06:41.488 --> 06:42.880
Change that back.

06:42.924 --> 06:44.534
I want to listen to music,
Aunt Birdie.

06:44.578 --> 06:46.884
♪ I could throw my lipstick
and bracelets like gravel ♪

06:46.928 --> 06:49.409
♪ And move to Alabama

06:49.452 --> 06:52.412
Give that to me,
before you stab your sister.

06:52.455 --> 06:54.414
♪ Then I died
a thousand times ♪

06:54.457 --> 06:55.980
He won't stab me.

06:56.024 --> 06:58.243
Well,
maybe not on purpose.

06:58.287 --> 07:00.550
♪♪

07:00.594 --> 07:04.162
I mean,
I like this one.

07:04.206 --> 07:09.341
♪♪

07:09.385 --> 07:11.343
[ Buzzer ]Do you have
any nicer boxes?

07:11.387 --> 07:13.084
It's for my mother.

07:13.476 --> 07:14.869
Uh...

07:17.785 --> 07:19.090
Pam!

07:19.134 --> 07:19.961
Shit!

07:20.004 --> 07:21.441
Julia,
in the back seat!

07:21.484 --> 07:23.878
Now!

07:23.921 --> 07:27.185
♪ He hung me
with the endless rope ♪

07:28.317 --> 07:29.797
Pam: Get down.
Settle down.

07:29.840 --> 07:31.189
[ Gun cocks ]

07:33.278 --> 07:34.410
Ohh!

07:34.454 --> 07:36.499
Whoo!

07:36.543 --> 07:37.892
Yes!

07:37.935 --> 07:39.763
Come on, come on,
come on, come on!

07:39.807 --> 07:41.069
[ Laughs ]

07:44.159 --> 07:46.683
Why would she do that to us,
man?

07:46.727 --> 07:51.166
I mean, why would she do
any of the shit she did to us?

07:51.209 --> 07:54.909
The question is what can
we do next?

07:54.952 --> 07:58.869
What about those bullshit
properties she gave us?

07:58.913 --> 08:01.219
We could sell those,
keep us going for a while.

08:01.263 --> 08:02.351
No, we can't.

08:02.394 --> 08:03.787
But why not, man?
I got a kid to feed.

08:03.831 --> 08:05.006
Because we need
those properties

08:05.049 --> 08:07.312
to launder money
from future jobs.

08:07.356 --> 08:09.967
We got to keep the books
straight.

08:10.011 --> 08:11.708
Maybe we should have asked
one of Pope's cousins

08:11.752 --> 08:14.624
where they stashed that gold
before we capped 'em all.

08:14.668 --> 08:19.324
Yeah, well, hindsight.

08:19.368 --> 08:22.327
That list of Smurf's assets,
the one the lawyer gave us,

08:22.371 --> 08:24.808
all the stuff that we got to
turn over to Pamela Johnson --

08:24.852 --> 08:27.158
there's a lot
that wasn't on that list.

08:27.202 --> 08:29.378
You just have all that
inventoried in your head?

08:29.421 --> 08:32.947
I'm just saying there's a lot
we can sell to get by.

08:32.990 --> 08:36.037
You met with
this lawyer before?

08:36.080 --> 08:38.561
I met her for the first time
today, same as you.

08:38.605 --> 08:41.521
♪♪

08:41.564 --> 08:43.044
What?

08:43.087 --> 08:44.654
I mean, she called to set
the meeting, but that's it.

08:44.698 --> 08:47.570
♪♪

08:47.614 --> 08:50.268
Whatever you say, J.

08:50.312 --> 08:51.922
[ Sighs ]

08:51.966 --> 08:53.533
What a shit show, man.

08:53.576 --> 08:56.448
♪♪

09:02.237 --> 09:03.499
Hey!

09:17.600 --> 09:19.297
Piece of shit!

09:21.735 --> 09:23.563
Hey, Craig.

09:23.606 --> 09:25.695
That baby is too cute.

09:25.739 --> 09:27.697
Thank you.

09:27.741 --> 09:29.003
Just stopping by
for a visit?

09:29.046 --> 09:31.266
Nah, I got some
Silicon Valley douchebags

09:31.309 --> 09:32.528
down at the marina
willing to pay

09:32.572 --> 09:35.096
San Francisco prices,
and I'm all out.

09:35.139 --> 09:37.054
Hmm.
Renn's a life saver.

09:49.110 --> 09:50.502
Hey. Shh.

09:50.546 --> 09:51.721
I just put him down.

09:51.765 --> 09:54.594
Uh-huh.

09:54.637 --> 09:56.334
What?

10:00.338 --> 10:01.557
You dealing
out of the house?

10:01.601 --> 10:04.429
It was Tonya.
She had an emergency.

10:04.473 --> 10:06.040
Oh,
cocaine emergency?

10:06.083 --> 10:08.259
I hope
everyone's okay.

10:09.957 --> 10:11.741
Get the bus home.

10:11.785 --> 10:13.743
We talked about this.

10:13.787 --> 10:15.440
It was a one-off.

10:15.484 --> 10:18.052
Some tech guys are having
a marathon poker game

10:18.095 --> 10:19.444
on their yacht.

10:19.488 --> 10:20.924
Ran out of
what Tonya had.

10:20.968 --> 10:22.230
So I did her a favor.

10:22.273 --> 10:24.624
Yeah, well, next time,
do her a favor somewhere

10:24.667 --> 10:25.929
where my kid isn't sleeping
in the room next door, okay?

10:25.973 --> 10:28.628
Hey. Calm down.
Oh, your kid?

10:33.807 --> 10:35.635
Just no more favors,alright?

10:48.822 --> 10:50.519
What?

10:52.347 --> 10:54.828
She cleaned me out.

10:54.871 --> 10:57.787
Five grand.

10:57.831 --> 11:01.704
Their boat's called
Byte Here and Now.

11:01.748 --> 11:04.098
B-Y-T-E.

11:04.141 --> 11:06.056
Jesus.

11:10.582 --> 11:11.671
Last time.

11:22.551 --> 11:24.118
♪♪

11:24.161 --> 11:25.510
There you go, pal.

11:25.554 --> 11:30.167
♪♪

11:30.211 --> 11:31.821
Is that
what I think it is?

11:31.865 --> 11:34.128
[ Sighs ]

11:34.171 --> 11:37.131
We need to
lay her to rest.

11:37.174 --> 11:38.262
Okay, alright.

11:38.306 --> 11:41.570
Meet me in my office.

11:41.613 --> 11:43.006
Back in a second.

11:43.050 --> 11:49.709
♪♪

11:49.752 --> 11:56.150
♪♪

11:56.193 --> 11:58.108
What's the rush?

11:58.152 --> 12:00.197
She's gone,
and we need to face it.

12:00.241 --> 12:01.546
I've been facing it.

12:01.590 --> 12:02.939
We were at the lawyer's office
this morning.

12:02.983 --> 12:04.027
Where were you?

12:04.071 --> 12:05.812
I was...busy.

12:05.855 --> 12:09.163
Smurf wrote that new will up
a couple weeks ago, okay?

12:09.206 --> 12:12.732
She's doing this shit to us
on purpose, man.

12:12.775 --> 12:14.559
Now, we can focus on giving her
a loving burial

12:14.603 --> 12:15.778
as soon as
we figure out a way

12:15.822 --> 12:18.085
to keep ourselves
from going homeless.

12:18.128 --> 12:24.047
♪♪

12:24.091 --> 12:30.053
♪♪

12:30.097 --> 12:31.794
Yo.Pope.

12:31.838 --> 12:34.057
♪♪

12:34.101 --> 12:35.580
Hey,
what's his problem?

12:35.624 --> 12:37.191
Deran: Same shit as always.
What's up?

12:37.234 --> 12:39.454
Yo, was he carrying
Smurf's ashes?

12:39.497 --> 12:41.238
Can you help me
with some kegs in the back?

12:41.282 --> 12:43.458
No. Later.Look.

12:43.501 --> 12:45.329
I got something for us now.

12:45.373 --> 12:46.766
-Right now?-Yeah.

12:46.809 --> 12:48.419
This shit is just getting
started. I can't.

12:48.463 --> 12:49.594
Well, get Tommy
to cover for you.

12:49.638 --> 12:52.597
It'll only take an hour.
Two, tops.

12:52.641 --> 12:55.252
Can you cover me right now?
Sorry, man.

12:55.296 --> 12:58.125
Let's go.

13:01.824 --> 13:03.739
[ Sighs ]

13:06.133 --> 13:12.922
♪♪

13:12.966 --> 13:19.842
♪♪

13:19.886 --> 13:26.718
♪♪

13:26.762 --> 13:29.460
Pam: [ Sighs ]

13:29.504 --> 13:33.638
You said you were gonna pawn
something, not rip the guy off.

13:33.682 --> 13:36.641
I don't get it. We used to
do this shit all the time.

13:36.685 --> 13:39.340
And that's how
I ended up in jail.

13:46.913 --> 13:49.654
I was gonna cut you in.

13:49.698 --> 13:51.221
It's not about that.

13:51.265 --> 13:55.269
My kids
need their mother.

13:55.312 --> 13:57.662
Phoenix took it hard
when I went away.

13:57.706 --> 14:00.665
And I still got to get my baby
girl back from foster care.

14:00.709 --> 14:03.799
I got lucky when I got
that plea deal last time.

14:03.843 --> 14:07.672
If I go back in,
I do real time.

14:07.716 --> 14:09.544
Okay.

14:12.025 --> 14:15.202
So,
what are we gonna do?

14:15.245 --> 14:18.553
Work at Denny's?

14:18.596 --> 14:22.252
I'm just pressing pause
for a minute.

14:22.296 --> 14:23.384
Trying some new shit.

14:23.427 --> 14:25.299
Been networking.

14:25.342 --> 14:27.083
What are you gonna
do for money?

14:27.127 --> 14:30.347
Make some.
What are you gonna do?

14:30.391 --> 14:33.220
You gonna live in your car
and rip off corner stores

14:33.263 --> 14:36.919
till those babies grow up
or you get caught?

14:36.963 --> 14:40.053
What's your plan?

14:40.096 --> 14:42.272
You were my plan.

14:42.316 --> 14:46.624
Better come up with another
because I'm out.

14:55.764 --> 14:58.332
I don't have anything going on
right now.

14:58.375 --> 15:01.204
That's not why I called.

15:01.248 --> 15:02.640
We need a fence.

15:02.684 --> 15:05.295
I thought you might
know someone.

15:05.339 --> 15:07.210
Things a little tight?

15:07.254 --> 15:09.038
I just need a name.

15:09.082 --> 15:10.605
What happened to Gia?

15:10.648 --> 15:13.738
She's not sure the Codys can
survive in a post-Smurf world?

15:16.089 --> 15:19.483
You know why
Smurf was so successful?

15:19.527 --> 15:22.747
Because
she had a network.

15:22.791 --> 15:25.054
Right now
I just need a fence.

15:25.098 --> 15:28.710
♪♪

15:28.753 --> 15:31.756
I know somebody.
I can make an introduction.

15:31.800 --> 15:33.236
Thank you.

15:33.280 --> 15:35.804
My end's 5%.

15:35.847 --> 15:37.240
Per transaction.

15:37.284 --> 15:41.244
♪♪

15:41.288 --> 15:44.421
Okay,
I'll talk to my uncles.

15:44.465 --> 15:46.554
Of course you will.

15:46.597 --> 15:48.251
Let me know
what they decide.

15:48.295 --> 15:57.869
♪♪

16:00.742 --> 16:03.788
Did you know about all the shit
Smurf had off the books?

16:03.832 --> 16:06.139
No. You?

16:06.182 --> 16:08.663
So, why does J
know about it?

16:13.624 --> 16:15.539
What are we looking for?
Here and Now?

16:15.583 --> 16:17.411
Byte Here and Now.

16:17.454 --> 16:25.027
♪♪

16:25.071 --> 16:32.469
♪♪

16:32.513 --> 16:39.868
♪♪

16:39.911 --> 16:41.913
Hate these assholesalready.

16:41.957 --> 16:50.096
♪♪

16:50.139 --> 16:58.278
♪♪

16:58.321 --> 17:06.460
♪♪

17:06.503 --> 17:11.508
♪♪

17:18.124 --> 17:19.386
-Call.
-Call what?

17:19.429 --> 17:20.735
Call your sister a whore?

17:20.778 --> 17:22.258
Show me your cards,
dickhead.

17:22.302 --> 17:23.520
Dude, show.
He called.

17:23.564 --> 17:26.175
What do you care?
You're out, man.

17:26.219 --> 17:29.178
Yo, you! Up! Now!Inside.

17:29.222 --> 17:30.353
-Get up.
-Right there!

17:30.397 --> 17:31.876
Down! Knees!Okay, okay, calm down!

17:31.920 --> 17:33.617
You on this boat
by yourself?

17:33.661 --> 17:34.879
-It's just us.-Hands.

17:34.923 --> 17:36.142
-Get on your knees.
-Right there.

17:36.185 --> 17:39.188
Craig: Get on your knees.

17:39.232 --> 17:40.972
You. Hands.

17:43.758 --> 17:46.543
-Ow!-Relax.

17:46.587 --> 17:47.718
Hey, we need
another phone.

17:47.762 --> 17:48.719
